# Project Brief

The "Project Brief" is the current session deliverable: user story & requirements. This serves as the "north star" to guide all development in the current session.

## File

`memory-bank/projectbrief.md`

## How to Create

Cleanly summarize the user's story and requirements for the current session.

If the user has not provided a complete picture of the work to be done, or there are ambiguities, prompt the user for more information.

## Format

Create the file in Markdown format, according to this template:

~~~markdown
# Project Brief

## User Story

As a(n) [role], I want to [goal] so that [benefit].

## Use-Case(s)

### Use-Case 1

### Use-Case 2

## Requirements

1. [requirement 1]
2. [requirement 2]
...

## Constraints

1. [constraint 1]
2. [constraint 2]
...

## Acceptance Criteria

1. [acceptance criterion 1]
2. [acceptance criterion 2]
...

~~~
